<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="42" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.9321/1</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">MacMurray</persName>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-11">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>May the notification of abrogation directed by Department’s
                                instruction of May 29 be explicitly confined to the second sentence
                                of Article 18 of the Treaty of 1858, which alone concerns arrest of
                                seamen?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>